OL,3,CCan Hamnet turn Shakespeare's tragedy
OL,4,Cinto Oscar gold?
OL,6,FAnd so history has suggested that the
OL,7,FShakespeare marriage was not a happy
OL,8,Fone, that the Bard abandoned Agnes and
OL,9,Fthe children and left her to deal with
OL,10,Fher unimaginable grief at the loss of
OL,11,Ftheir son.
OL,13,FThe book and now the film fills the
OL,14,Fgaps in the history in a different way.
OL,16,FThe family are presented as loving,
OL,17,Fthe couple as passionate, the terrible
OL,18,Fbereavement affecting both parents
OL,19,Fequally, in fact inspiring the Bard to
OL,20,Fwrite one of the most famous works
OL,21,Fever, Hamlet.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
